        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 3:30PM EDT until June 27 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>SVRRLX

The National Weather Service in Charleston West Virginia has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Raleigh County in southeastern West Virginia...

* Until 400 PM EDT.

* At 329 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Flat Top, or
7 miles north of Camp Creek, and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Shady Spring and Ghent.

This includes West Virginia Turnpike between mile markers 28 and 30.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
